OL,3,CExercise can help cut risk of 'baby
OL,4,Cblues' ` study
OL,6,FNew mothers can reduce the risk of
OL,7,Fdeveloping postnatal depression if
OL,8,Fthey can find time to exercise for
OL,9,Fmore than an hour every week,
OL,10,Faccording to a new study.
OL,12,FExercising for at least 80 minutes
OL,13,Feach week could also help reduce
OL,14,Fsymptoms among new mothers who have
OL,15,Fdepression or anxiety, researchers
OL,16,Ffound.
OL,18,FBut they should balance exercise with
OL,19,Ftheir recovery from childbirth,
OL,20,Fexperts said.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/8
